Absolutely, you can achieve horizontal scrolling in Jetpack Compose without enabling the default dragging behavior. One approach is to use a `HorizontalScroll` modifier while controlling the drag gesture.

To do this, you can create a scrollable layout using `Row` and wrap it in a `Modifier.horizontalScroll` but then override the drag behavior. Here’s a quick example:

```kotlin
val scrollState = rememberScrollState()

Row(
    modifier = Modifier
        .horizontalScroll(scrollState)
        .pointerInput(Unit) {
            // Disabling touch events that initiate dragging
            detectDragGestures(
                onDragStart = { },
                onDragEnd = { }
            )
        }
) {
    // Add your items here
}
```

In this setup, the Row will allow horizontal scrolling via touch input, but the dragging gestures will be ignored, maintaining control over how the users interact with the component.

