It sounds like you're running into a frustrating issue with the "FocusRequestor not initialized" error. This can happen if the `TextField` or the associated focus handling isn't properly set up.

One common way to ensure that focus is properly managed is to create a `FocusRequester` and tie it to your `TextField`. Here’s an example of how you might do that:

```kotlin
@Composable
fun SimpleDropdown(options: List<String>, selectedOption: String, onOptionSelected: (String) -> Unit) {
    var expanded by remember { mutableStateOf(false) }
    val focusRequester = remember { FocusRequester() }

    ExposedDropdownMenuBox(expanded = expanded, onExpandedChange = { expanded = !expanded }) {
        TextField(
            readOnly = true,
            value = selectedOption,
            onValueChange = {},
            label = { Text("Select an option") },
            trailingIcon = {
                IconButton(onClick = { expanded = !expanded }) {
                    Icon(Icons.Default.ArrowDropDown, contentDescription = null)
                }
            },
            modifier = Modifier
                .focusRequester(focusRequester)
                .clickable(onClick = { expanded = !expanded }) // Ensure clicking also toggles
        )
        ExposedDropdownMenu(
            expanded = expanded,
            onDismissRequest = { expanded = false }
        ) {
            options.forEach { option ->
                DropdownMenuItem(onClick = {
                    onOptionSelected(option)
                    expanded = false
                }) {
                    Text(option)
                }
            }
        }
    }

    // Optionally request focus if the TextField is displayed
    LaunchedEffect(Unit) {
        focusRequester.requestFocus()
    }
}
```

By incorporating a `FocusRequester`, you can help ensure that the focus management is correctly initialized and that the dropdown behaves as intended. I hope this helps resolve the issue! If you keep experiencing problems, feel free to ask for further assistance—I'm here to support you!
